-- Germany Convinces India to Cut Iran Oil Imports, Focus Says
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2012-01-28T15:59:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-28/germany-convinces-india-to-cut-iran-oil-imports-focus-says.html
Germany  managed to convince  India  to
reduce its crude imports from  Iran  a few days ago before
 Chancellor Angela Merkel  seeks support in  China  next week for
the European Union’s ban on the country’s oil,  Focus  magazine
reported, citing an adviser to Merkel it didn’t identify.  The aim is to get China at least not to increase its
imports from Iran, the magazine cited the adviser as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
